The paper discusses the use of intelligent control of autonomous vehicles to dampen traffic waves, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). The experiments were conducted on a circular track, which suggests the involvement of robotics (cs.RO) and civil engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper mentions metrics for fuel economy, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) in terms of optimizing resource allocation.
